"title": "7725: evangelists, identity of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7725: evangelists, identity of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Some OT figures announced good news, but most evangelists are seen in the NT. The task was first given by Jesus Christ to the apostles and then to other believers. All Christians have a part in evangelism; there is, too, a special role of evangelist within the church, fulfilled by those with a particular gifting from the Holy Spirit.</p>\n<h2>An evangelist as one who announces good news</h2>\n<h3>God as an announcer of good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:8\">GAL 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2-Gen12:3\">GEN 12:2–12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:18\">GEN 22:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:4\">GEN 26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:3-Jer31:4\">JER 31:3–31:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:36\">ACT 10:36</a></p>\n<h3>OT messengers announce good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:2-Ps96:3\">PSA 96:2–96:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:23-1Chr16:24\">1CH 16:23–16:24</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:9\">ISA 40:9</a></strong> <em>The good news of the end of the Babylonian exile.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:9\">2KI 7:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:10\">PSA 40:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:1-Isa40:5\">ISA 40:1–40:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:27\">ISA 41:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:7\">ISA 52:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:15\">NAM 1:15</a> <em>the good news of the deliverance from Assyria</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41\">MAT 12:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:32\">LUK 11:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:15\">ROM 10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:5\">2PE 2:5</a></p>\n<h3>Angels announce good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:10-Luke2:11\">LUK 2:10–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:19\">LUK 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:6\">REV 14:6</a></p>\n<h3>John the Baptist announces good news</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:18\">LUK 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3\">LUK 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:16\">LUK 16:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as an evangelist</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:35\">MAT 9:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:14-Mark1:15\">MRK 1:14–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:43\">LUK 4:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:1\">LUK 8:1</a></p>\n<h2>The disciples as evangelists</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ sends out the Twelve</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14\">MRK 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:7-Matt10:8\">MAT 10:7–10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:2\">LUK 9:1–9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:6\">LUK 9:6</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ commissions the apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:15\">MRK 16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:18–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:47\">LUK 24:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>The evangelism of the apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:42\">ACT 5:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:25\">ACT 8:25</a> <em>Peter and John preach the gospel in Samaria</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:7\">ACT 15:7</a> <em>Peter preaches the gospel to Cornelius.</em></p>\n<h2>Other believers as evangelists</h2>\n<h3>Evangelists are gifted by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Paul as an evangelist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:24\">ACT 20:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:9\">ROM 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:19-Rom15:20\">ROM 15:19–15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17\">1CO 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:12\">2CO 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:7\">GAL 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Philip the evangelist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:8\">ACT 21:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:5\">ACT 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:12\">ACT 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:35\">ACT 8:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:40\">ACT 8:40</a></p>\n<h3>Other evangelists</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:4\">ACT 8:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:5\">2TI 4:5</a></strong> <em>Timothy's calling includes that of an evangelist.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:20\">MRK 5:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:39\">LUK 8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28-John4:29\">JHN 4:28–4:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:26\">ACT 18:26</a> <em>Priscilla and Aquila</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15\">1PE 3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Evangelists within the family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:19\">MRK 5:19</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:16\">1CO 7:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:2\">1PE 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:4\">EPH 6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:5\">2TI 1:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:6\">TIT 1:6</a></p>",
